  "texts": [
    "CNNs consist of convolution layers and pooling layers.",
    "In each convolution layer, a learnable kernel g is used to learn local features of the data.",
    "Typically, a pooling layer is used immediately after each convolution layer to aggregate the local information of the output of the convolution layer and select the most concise and efficient features.",
    "The general formulation of CNN is provided in Eqs.",
    "(24)-(26),"
